        "segment": "Container orchestration platforms like Kubernetes manage the deployment and scaling of software components by automating the scheduling, deployment, and scaling of containerized applications across a cluster of machines.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Unlike traditional virtual machine deployments, which involve managing entire operating systems and virtual hardware, Kubernetes focuses on managing lightweight containers that package only the application and its dependencies.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Kubernetes provides features such as automatic load balancing, self-healing by restarting failed containers, and declarative configuration for desired state management, enabling more efficient resource utilization and faster deployment cycles compared to traditional VM-based approaches.",
        "citations": []
    }
]

